{
  "texts": [
    "For the more general models performing largely unsupervised learning, these data are already being generated at an accelerating rate.",
    "For those requiring more specific labelled data, this is accelerating, but the rate of generation remains lower.",
    "Relative data gaps exist and some targeted data generation could have an outsized impact on risks.",
    "Some models use state-of-the-art highly optimised machine learning techniques while others do not.",
    "It is common for newly released and less-optimised models to quickly be upgraded by others with alterations that are more standard in adjacent fields."
  ]
}